comment:
* Helper class for reporting boot and shutdown timing metrics. * *

NOTE: This class is not thread-safe. Use a separate copy for other threads. * * @hide

variables.name: DEBUG_BOOT_TIME
variables.comment: Debug boot time for every step if it's non-user build.

variables.name: MAX_NESTED_CALLS
variables.comment: Maximum number of nested calls that are stored

methods.name: public void traceBegin(String name)
methods.comment:
* Begin tracing named section
     * @param name name to appear in trace

methods.name: public void traceEnd()
methods.comment:
* End tracing previously {@link #traceBegin(String) started} section. * *

Also {@link #logDuration logs} the duration.

methods.name: public void logDuration(String name, long timeMs)
methods.comment: * Logs a duration so it can be parsed by external tools for performance reporting.

methods.name: public final List<String> getUnfinishedTracesForDebug()
methods.comment:
* Gets the names of the traces that {@link #traceBegin(String) have begun} but * {@link #traceEnd() have not finished} yet. * *

NOTE: this method is expensive and it should not be used in "production" - it * should only be used for debugging purposes during development (and/or guarded by * static {@code DEBUG} constants that are {@code false}).

methodNames: public void logDuration(String name, long timeMs)
